  "generated_text": "To determine how many years it takes to start earning money, we need to compare the total cost of planting the tree against the total revenue from selling the lemons.\n\n**1. Identify the costs and revenues:**\n*   **Planting Cost:** $\\$90$ (One-time cost).\n*   **Annual Water/Feed Cost:** $\\$3$ per year.\n*   **Lemon Yield per year:** $7$ lemons.\n*   **Selling Price per lemon:** $\\$1.50$.\n\n**2. Calculate the profit per year (excluding the initial planting cost):**\nFirst, find the total revenue generated in one year:\n$$ \\text{Annual Revenue} = 7 \\text{ lemons} \\times \\$1.50/\\text{lemon} = \\$10.50 $$\n\nNext, find the total annual operating cost:\n$$ \\text{Annual Operating Cost} = \\$3/\\text{year} $$\n\nCalculate the net profit for the first year:\n$$ \\text{Net Profit} = \\text{Annual Revenue} - \\text{Annual Operating Cost} $$\n$$ \\text{Net Profit} = \\$10.50 - \\$3 = \\$7.50 $$\n\n**3. Determine when the initial cost is recovered:**\nSince the tree costs $\\$90$ to plant, the first year only generates $\\$7.50$ in profit. The tree will not break even in the first year. It will take multiple years of this profit to cover the $\\$90$ planting cost.\n\nWe calculate the number of full years required to recover the cost by dividing the total cost by the annual net profit:\n$$ \\text{Years needed} = \\frac{\\text{Total Cost}}{\\text{Annual Net Profit}} $$\n$$ \\text{Years needed} = \\frac{90}{7.5} $$\n\nTo simplify the division:\n$$ \\frac{90}{7.5} = \\frac{900}{75} $$\nDivide both numerator and denominator by 25:\n$$ \\frac{900 \\div 25}{75 \\div 25} = \\frac{36}{3} = 12 $$\n\nSo, it takes exactly 12 years to recover the initial $\\$90$ investment.\n*   **Year 1:** Profit $\\$7.50$ (Total Cost $\\$90$, Remaining Balance $\\$82.50$)\n*   **Year 2:** Profit $\\$7.50$ (Total Cost $\\$90$, Remaining Balance $\\$75.00$)\n*   ...\n*   **Year 12:** Profit $\\$7.50$ (Total Cost $\\$90$, Remaining Balance $\\$0$)\n\nAt the end of year 12, the initial planting cost is fully recovered. This means he starts earning money (specifically, his profit) on",
